A walker and a jogger travel along the same straight line in the same
direction. The walker walks at one meter per second, while the jogger runs at
two meters per second. The jogger starts one meter in front of the walker. A
dog starts with the walker, and then runs back and forth between the walker and
the jogger with constant speed of three meters per second. Let $f(n)$ meters
denote the total distance travelled by the dog when it has returned to the
walker for the $n$ th time (so $f(0) = 0$). Find a formula for $f(n)$.
